The paper deals with the problem of zero-error capacity for finite state channels with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of dynamic programming to solve the problem suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY) or dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of iterative algorithms. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) due to the application of the results to communication networks.
